{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"766c9c50-7ab1-45ba-93dc-4717980d1c18","content":"I can help point you in the right direction! The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so it won't apply here.\n\nFor **analyzing** a `.dmp` file from a .NET app, use one of these tools:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — cross-platform, SOS-based commands like `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, etc.\n2. **`lldb` + SOS plugin** — on Linux/macOS for deeper native + managed debugging.\n3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio** — on Windows.\n\n**Quick triage with `dotnet-dump`:**\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n\n# Inside the REPL, try:\n> pe              # print last exception\n> clrstack -all   # managed call stacks for all threads\n> dumpheap -stat  # heap summary\n```\n\nThe `pe` (print exception) command is usually the fastest way to find the crash root cause. Would you like help with any specific step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e113c0d7-795a-4d98-aefd-0f1059ddf8e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill doesn't apply here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":398,"requestId":"9424:28DE61:195F799:1CC1218:69E82103"},"id":"c940f1c4-5797-4526-82ca-95c2e63ec650","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:14:55.494Z","parentId":"fba45c13-07c3-4114-b68f-f57a7d38074b"}
